From e9c1106d522235be6c6f5d56dddd19293e9d740e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 16:33:39 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase D polish: bump sticky diff header z-index above review
 widgets

Reported: native review-comment widgets render above the sticky
diff card headers as the user scrolls.

Monaco's `commentThreadZoneWidget` and the underlying
`zoneWidget` are layered at z-index 10 (thread frames) and 20
(resize/action overlays). My sticky header was at z-index 5 --
under both -- so a thread anchored near the top of the file
floated over the sticky header.

Bump the header to z-index 30, comfortably above the review
layer. Documented the reasoning + paths in the CSS comment so the
next reader knows what we're racing.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 .../contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css   | 8 +++++---
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css b/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css
index 2af0801889f..e0926ee9c86 100644
--- a/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css
+++ b/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css
@@ -844,11 +844,13 @@
 	/* Sticks to the top of the outer pane scroll while the user is
 	 * inside this file's diff. When the user scrolls past the card,
 	 * the next card's sticky header takes over naturally. z-index
-	 * above the editor's overlay so the header isn't covered by
-	 * Monaco's gutter / minimap. */
+	 * has to beat Monaco's review-thread zone widgets (z-index 10
+	 * for thread frames, 20 for the resize/action overlays inside
+	 * them — see vs/workbench/contrib/comments/browser/media/
+	 * review.css). 30 keeps us comfortably above. */
 	position: sticky;
 	top: 0;
-	z-index: 5;
+	z-index: 30;
 }
 
 .krt-pr-flat-diff-head:hover {
